    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sancte et individue trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/130">Heinricus</persName> divina [favente] clementia
                        Romanorum <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. Si locis divino
                        cultui mancipatis proprietates pertinentias et legum instituta augere
                        defensare et confirmare studuerimus, [id] non solum humana laude
                        predicandum, verum etiam divina remuneratione nobis recompensandum credimus
                        et etiam scimus. Quapropter agnoscant omnes fideles nostri presentes atque
                        futuri, qualiter nos pro dei omnipotentis amore animeque nostre absolutione
                        nec non interventu vel petitione domni <persName key="#Archbishops"
                            ref="#people/1583">Arnaldi</persName>
                        <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1471"
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma #Offersio/donatio #Cities #Rivers #Massae #Penalty #Castle #Tower #Ports #Comitatus #Dioecesis #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio #Churches #Monasteries"
                            >sancte <placeName ref="#places/594">Rauennatis</placeName>
                            ecclesie</orgName> venerabilis <rs key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopi</rs>
                        sue sancte sedi per hanc nostram preceptalem paginam confirmamus et
                        firmissime corroboramus omnes illo pertinentes <rs key="#Dioecesis"
                            >episcopatus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasteria</rs>
                        <rs key="#Churches">ecclesias</rs>
                        <rs key="#Cities">civitates</rs> et <rs key="#Castle">castella</rs> ac omnes
                        res, que unquam per <rs key="#Diploma">cartulas antiquas privilegia</rs>
                        atque precepta ad eandem sacrosanctam Rauennatem ecclesiam pertinuerunt,
                        insuper et ea que in nostri diadematis temporibus vel antea a <persName
                            key="#Popes">Iohanne</persName> papa vel a <persName key="#Popes"
                            ref="#people/1636">Gregorio</persName>
                        <rs key="#Popes">papa</rs> ad ipsam ecclesiam sunt oblata et perpetualiter
                        donata et a nobis confirmata, videlicet <rs key="#Comitatus">comitatum</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Castle" ref="#places/1890"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/1479">Cesenatem</geogName></placeName> cum <rs
                            key="#Castle">castro veteri et novo</rs> et <rs key="#Tower"
                            >turribus</rs> et omnibus sibi pertinentibus, comitatum <placeName
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters" ref="#places/4667"
                                ><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/3913"><orgName
                                    key="#Dioecesis">Ficoclensem</orgName></geogName></placeName>
                        cum <rs key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">ripa</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Dioecesis">episcopatu</rs> suo simulque comitatum <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/3987"
                                >Decimanum</geogName></placeName>, comitatum <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus"><geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/3988"
                                >Trauersarie</geogName></placeName>, comitatum <placeName
                            key="#Comitatus" ref="#places/3512"><geogName key="#Comitatus"
                                ref="#estates/2409">Imolensem</geogName></placeName>, <rs
                            key="#Massae">massam</rs> que vocatur <placeName key="#Massae"
                            ref="#places/4600"><geogName key="#Massae" ref="#estates/2479"
                                >Fiscalia</geogName></placeName> cum <placeName ref="#places/3520"
                            >Corna ceruina</placeName>, <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/1460">sancte Marie in
                            Pomposa</orgName>, monasterium <orgName key="#Monasteries">sancti
                            Illarii in Galliata</orgName> cum omni <rs key="#Districtio"
                            >districtione placitoque</rs> suo nec non districtum Rauenne cum <rs
                            key="#Ports">portis</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">ripa</rs> muris
                        publicariis omnibus <rs key="#Teloneum">teloneis</rs> moneta et omnem
                        potestatem in omnibus in Rauenna et extra Rauennam civitatem, monasterium
                            <orgName key="#Monasteries">sancti Thome apostoli</orgName>, monasterium
                            <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/3668">sancte
                            Euphemie</orgName> infra civitatem <placeName ref="#places/1806"
                            >Ariminensem</placeName> cum omnibus pertinentiis eorum seu omnes res,
                        quascumque <rs key="#Deacons">diaconus</rs>
                        <persName key="#Deacons"><name ref="Petrus">Petrus</name></persName> filius
                        <persName key="#Marquis/duke"><name ref="Martinus">Martini</name></persName> 
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">ducis</rs> per cartulam <rs key="#Offersio/donatio">donationis</rs> in
                        sanctam Rauennatem ecclesiam tradidit et quascunque <persName
                            key="#Countess"><name ref="Ingelrada">Inglerada</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Countess">comitissa</rs> detinuit, sicut <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/173">Otto</persName> imperator in
                        placito <persName key="#Archbishops"><name ref="Petrus"
                            >Petro</name></persName> Rauennati archiepiscopo legaliter investivit et
                        in perpetuum confirmavit, itemque omnes res et posessiones, quas
                                <persName><name ref="Lambertus">Lambertus</name></persName> cum
                        uxore et filiis suis habuerunt a mari usque ad Alpes, a <rs key="#Rivers"
                            >fluvio</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/3548">Reno</placeName> usque ad
                            <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/4609">Foliam</placeName>, sicut
                        nos in prefata ecclesia olim tradidimus, quoniam inimici rei publice et
                        sancte Rauennatis ecclesie facti sunt, -- atque hec omnia in omnibus, sicut
                        iam confirmavimus et olim confirmata fuerunt, prefato Arnaldo archiepiscopo
                        et ad suos successores in perpetuum stabilimus. Unde imperiali statuimus
                        edicto, ut, si aliquis dux marchio comes vicecomes seu ulla nostri imperii
                        magna parvaque persona eandem Rauennatem ecclesiam disvestierit seu
                        molestaverit, <rs key="#Penalty">centum libras auri cocti componat</rs>,
                        medietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis">camare</rs> nostre et medietatem <rs
                            key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">prescripto archiepiscopo</rs>
                        suis que successoribus. Quod ut verius credatur, hanc paginam manu propria
                        roborantes sigillo nostro sigillari iussimus. Signum domni Heinrici
                        serenissimi imperatoris augusti. (M.) <persName key="#Chancellor"><name
                                ref="Heinricus">Heinricus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> vice <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops"><name ref="Everardus"
                            >Euerardi</name></persName> episcopi et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> recognovit. Datum anno dominice incarnacionis
                        millesimo XIIII, indictione XII, anno vero domni Heinrici imperatoris
                        augusti regnantis XII, imperii eius primo; actum
                            <placeName>Subtrio</placeName>; feliciter.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
